---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---
<Page
  title="Our Teachers"
  heroTitle="Our Teachers"
  heroSubtitle="Stillwater's teachers bring decades of practice and study across multiple Buddhist traditions."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="teachers-list">

        <div class="teacher-profile">
          <div class="teacher-profile-img">
            <img
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508214751196-bcfd4ca60f91?w=400&q=80"
              alt="Sarah Morrison"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="teacher-profile-body">
            <h2>Sarah Morrison</h2>
            <p class="teacher-role">Senior Teacher &amp; Founder</p>
            <p>
              Sarah has practised and studied within the Tibetan Buddhist tradition for
              over twenty-five years, with extended periods of training in India and Nepal.
              She holds a deep connection with both the Kagyu and Nyingma lineages and has
              completed two three-year retreats under the guidance of senior Tibetan masters.
            </p>
            <p>
              Sarah is known for her ability to make the subtlest teachings accessible to
              contemporary Western students. She draws on both classical texts and her own
              sustained experience to offer teachings that are precise, warm, and immediately
              useful. She founded Stillwater in 2019 with the intention of creating a
              genuinely welcoming home for contemplative practice in the Hudson Valley.
            </p>
            <p>
              When she is not teaching, Sarah leads silent retreats and writes on the
              relationship between meditation and mental health.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="teacher-profile">
          <div class="teacher-profile-img">
            <img
              src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506794778202-cad84cf45f1d?w=400&q=80"
              alt="David Chen"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="teacher-profile-body">
            <h2>David Chen</h2>
            <p class="teacher-role">Meditation Instructor</p>
            <p>
              David came to meditation through his work as a clinical psychologist, where
              he observed first-hand the profound effects of mindfulness-based interventions
              on mental health. Seeking a deeper foundation, he spent five years studying with
              teachers in the Tibetan Gelug tradition and later trained in Soto Zen with
              teachers in Japan and the United States.
            </p>
            <p>
              David brings a unique perspective that bridges the contemplative and scientific
              traditions. His teaching style is practical, evidence-informed, and rooted in
              a genuine appreciation of the classical sources. He leads Stillwater's
              Introduction to Meditation and Mindful Living courses, and is particularly
              skilled at working with those who come to practice through an interest in
              mental health and wellbeing.
            </p>
            <p>
              David also leads mindfulness programmes for healthcare professionals and
              community organisations throughout the Hudson Valley.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>

<style>
  .teachers-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5rem; }
  .teacher-profile { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr; gap: 3.5rem; align-items: start; }
  .teacher-profile-img { border-radius: var(--radius-xl); overflow: hidden; aspect-ratio: 3/4; }
  .teacher-profile-img img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center top; }
  .teacher-profile-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: var(--font-size-3xl); font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .teacher-role { font-size: var(--font-size-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .teacher-profile-body p { font-size: var(--font-size-base); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .teacher-profile { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .teacher-profile-img { max-width: 200px; }
  }
</style>
